Package: tmjmenu
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         python3 (>= 3.10),
         python3-gi,
         python3-xlib,
         gir1.2-gtk-4.0,
         gir1.2-adw-1,
         xdotool
Recommends: tmjos-branding
Description: TMJOs proprietary application menu + dock
 Replaces Plank dock and GNOME Activities Overview with two integrated
 components, both GTK4 + libadwaita native (same stack as TMJPad):
 .
   * tmjmenu — popup search launcher, opened by Super key
   * tmjdock — bottom-centered dock with pinned apps + central TMJOs
     button that opens tmjmenu
 .
 Postinst disables /etc/xdg/autostart/plank.desktop (if present) so
 tmjdock takes over without two docks fighting for screen space.
 The Plank package itself is left installed (tmjos-dock scripts like
 tmjos-first-run remain functional).
 .
 Wayland support deferred to v2.0 (will use gtk4-layer-shell instead
 of X11 hints).
